Ingress is a Kubernetes resource that manages external HTTP/HTTPS traffic routing into your cluster services.

Ingress Controller nothing but pod that should be created to route the traffic and we can define rules in Ingress resource.
--------------------------------
Ingress Resource does NOT run like a pod.

What Ingress Resource Actually Is
It is just a configuration file / set of rules — like a routing table. It tells the Ingress Controller how to route traffic, but it doesn't run anything itself.
-------------------------------------------
How It Works Together
---------------------------------------
User Request
     ↓
Ingress Controller (Running Pod - NGINX)
     ↓ reads rules from
Ingress Resource (Your ingress.yaml)
     ↓ routes to
Service (api-service or web-service)
     ↓
Your App Pods

